The Witches describe sending out a storm on a sailor’s ship so that he can’t sleep. This could
be read as a metaphor for what will happen to Macbeth, who’s made sleepless by guilt, and the
ship could be a metaphor for Scotland, which is almost destroyed during Macbeth’s violent reign.
